<item>
            <title>[JDK-8340824] C2: Memory for TypeInterfaces not reclaimed by hashcons()</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8340824</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>The list of interfaces for a TypeInterfaces is contained in a GrowableArray that&amp;#39;s allocated in the type arena. When hashcons() deletes a TypeInterfaces object because an identical one exists, it can&amp;#39;t reclaim memory for the object because it can only free the last thing that was allocated and that&amp;#39;s the backing store for the GrowableArray, not the TypeInterfaces object.</description>
